{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01TPr76CoMHHdWsh9viV1c3b","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Build user profile page\n     2→\n     3→## Context\n     4→The PLAN says \"Users should have a profile page similar to like a youtube profile.\" The backend already has all the queries needed (`users.getByUsername`, `themes.getByAuthor`, `stars.getStarredThemes`, `users.updateProfile`), but there is no frontend page. Author names on the homepage gallery cards and theme detail page are plain text — not links. This is a critical MVP gap: users who create themes have no public presence on the site.\n     5→\n     6→## Requirements\n     7→\n     8→### 1. Create the profile page route at `app/src/app/user/[username]/page.tsx`\n     9→- Fetch user by username via `api.users.getByUsername`\n    10→- Show 404-style message if user not found\n    11→- Display: avatar (or initial fallback), display name, username, bio\n    12→- Show the user's public themes using `api.themes.getByAuthor` in a grid of ThemeCards (reuse the same card style as the homepage)\n    13→- Show the user's starred themes using `api.stars.getStarredThemes` in a separate tab or section\n    14→- Include theme count and star count stats\n    15→- If the viewer is the profile owner, show an \"Edit Profile\" button that allows editing displayName and bio via `api.users.updateProfile`\n    16→\n    17→### 2. Make author names link to profiles\n    18→- **Homepage (`app/src/app/page.tsx`)**: The author name in `ThemeCard` should link to `/user/{username}`. The `useQuery(api.users.get, ...)` call already returns username — wrap the author name in a `<Link>`.\n    19→- **Theme detail page (`app/src/app/theme/[slug]/page.tsx`)**: The \"by {author}\" line should link to `/user/{username}`.\n    20→- Links should use `event.stopPropagation()` or be nested correctly so clicking the author name navigates to the profile, not the theme.\n    21→\n    22→### 3. Include site header consistency\n    23→- Use the same header pattern as the theme detail page (ThemeDrops logo link, CreateThemeLink, AuthControls).\n    24→\n    25→## Backend queries already available\n    26→- `users.getByUsername({ username })` — returns full user doc\n    27→- `users.getCurrentUser()` — returns current signed-in user\n    28→- `users.updateProfile({ displayName?, bio?, avatarUrl? })` — mutation\n    29→- `themes.getByAuthor({ authorId })` — returns user's themes (filters private unless viewer is owner)\n    30→- `stars.getStarredThemes({ userId })` — returns themes the user has starred\n    31→\n    32→## Important notes\n    33→- `users.get` (used on homepage cards) returns `{ _id, username, displayName, avatarUrl }` — username is already available for building the link URL\n    34→- The `getByUsername` query returns the full user doc including `bio` — but does NOT filter sensitive fields. Only display: `_id`, `username`, `displayName`, `bio`, `avatarUrl`.\n    35→- Keep the design consistent with the existing pages (gray-50 bg, white cards, same typography scale)\n    36→- The profile page should look good even if the user has zero themes\n    37→\n    38→## Acceptance criteria\n    39→- [ ] `/user/{username}` renders a profile page with user info and their themes\n    40→- [ ] Visiting a non-existent username shows a \"User not found\" message\n    41→- [ ] Author names on homepage cards link to `/user/{username}`\n    42→- [ ] Author name on theme detail page links to `/user/{username}`\n    43→- [ ] Profile owner can edit their display name and bio inline\n    44→- [ ] Page includes consistent site header with nav back to home\n    45→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"2ee1c275-4822-470d-95d7-c91f2b4b25ff","uuid":"ca356e50-758c-4655-bd22-7a7dd7ad9f22","timestamp":"2026-03-28T00:02:16.638Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/matt/code/themedrops/swarm/tasks/user-profile-page.todo.md","content":"# Build user profile page\n\n## Context\nThe PLAN says \"Users should have a profile page similar to like a youtube profile.\" The backend already has all the queries needed (`users.getByUsername`, `themes.getByAuthor`, `stars.getStarredThemes`, `users.updateProfile`), but there is no frontend page. Author names on the homepage gallery cards and theme detail page are plain text — not links. This is a critical MVP gap: users who create themes have no public presence on the site.\n\n## Requirements\n\n### 1. Create the profile page route at `app/src/app/user/[username]/page.tsx`\n- Fetch user by username via `api.users.getByUsername`\n- Show 404-style message if user not found\n- Display: avatar (or initial fallback), display name, username, bio\n- Show the user's public themes using `api.themes.getByAuthor` in a grid of ThemeCards (reuse the same card style as the homepage)\n- Show the user's starred themes using `api.stars.getStarredThemes` in a separate tab or section\n- Include theme count and star count stats\n- If the viewer is the profile owner, show an \"Edit Profile\" button that allows editing displayName and bio via `api.users.updateProfile`\n\n### 2. Make author names link to profiles\n- **Homepage (`app/src/app/page.tsx`)**: The author name in `ThemeCard` should link to `/user/{username}`. The `useQuery(api.users.get, ...)` call already returns username — wrap the author name in a `<Link>`.\n- **Theme detail page (`app/src/app/theme/[slug]/page.tsx`)**: The \"by {author}\" line should link to `/user/{username}`.\n- Links should use `event.stopPropagation()` or be nested correctly so clicking the author name navigates to the profile, not the theme.\n\n### 3. Include site header consistency\n- Use the same header pattern as the theme detail page (ThemeDrops logo link, CreateThemeLink, AuthControls).\n\n## Backend queries already available\n- `users.getByUsername({ username })` — returns full user doc\n- `users.getCurrentUser()` — returns current signed-in user\n- `users.updateProfile({ displayName?, bio?, avatarUrl? })` — mutation\n- `themes.getByAuthor({ authorId })` — returns user's themes (filters private unless viewer is owner)\n- `stars.getStarredThemes({ userId })` — returns themes the user has starred\n\n## Important notes\n- `users.get` (used on homepage cards) returns `{ _id, username, displayName, avatarUrl }` — username is already available for building the link URL\n- The `getByUsername` query returns the full user doc including `bio` — but does NOT filter sensitive fields. Only display: `_id`, `username`, `displayName`, `bio`, `avatarUrl`.\n- Keep the design consistent with the existing pages (gray-50 bg, white cards, same typography scale)\n- The profile page should look good even if the user has zero themes\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n- [ ] `/user/{username}` renders a profile page with user info and their themes\n- [ ] Visiting a non-existent username shows a \"User not found\" message\n- [ ] Author names on homepage cards link to `/user/{username}`\n- [ ] Author name on theme detail page links to `/user/{username}`\n- [ ] Profile owner can edit their display name and bio inline\n- [ ] Page includes consistent site header with nav back to home\n","numLines":45,"startLine":1,"totalLines":45}}}
